Do not read this story, it's too depressing.It's the usual (and I hate to say 'the usual' - but these stories seem to pop up with regular frequency) pedophile cop story but then there's this paragraph:quote:On one wall is a "Star Trek" poster with investigators' faces substituted for the Starship Enterprise crew. But even that alludes to a dark fact of their work: All but one of the offenders they have arrested in the last four years was a hard-core Trekkie. emphasis addedSo, anyway, I have nothing interesting to say about it. It's just one of those weird bits of random data that just pops up from time to time, and......well, like I said, I don't really know what to make of it.(I suppose this will be inflammatory to Trek fans, but I would like to caveat that I'm a pretty big fan myself, so it's not like I'm picking on anyone.)The cop theorizes that "It has something to do with a fantasy world where mutants and monsters have power and where the usual rules don't apply," Bulmer reflects. "But beyond that, I can't really explain it."But that could be said of a lot of people into the various type fantasies and sci-fi's that people are into......Just a bit of weird in what is otherwise a tragically awful story. (You may not commence posting your revenge ideas on pedophiles. I'll let you decide whether your fantasty barbarism is any less tragic and brutish than the pedophiles themselves. I feel the same way, but I don't feel good about it.)
