Posted: Fri Apr 29, 2005 9:12 pm
I wonder if the underlying connection between Star-Trek and child-sexual predation is actually technology.I was actually reading an article in the Age today (it's probably on the web site, but I can't be bothered finding it) which was talking about some child porn found on a computer at a community centre. They quoted the head of the police unit responsible for investigating such things, and he mentioned that, despite hundreds of arrests for posessing child pornography, they'd never had any evidence that any of it was locally produced. Most of it seemed to come from Eastern Europe, apparently.Presumably, peadophiles have always had ways of copying and distributing their pictures, even before computers. But I could imagine that they would be highly-motivated early adopters of things like email, encryption, P2P networks, and so on. Who would be surprised to hear, for example, that peadophiles have private BitTorrent trackers for distributing pictures and movies (I have no idea if they actually do, mind you)?There is a lot of overlap between other early technology adopters and Trekkies. I remember the script for Star Trek: Generations being the hottest items on every (non-Internet connected) BBS when it appeared a few months before the movie was released. Hell, in its early years UseNet was essentially a dedicated Trek-discussion network. Maybe paedophiles, moving in techological circles, are no different to other tech users (I don't want to sullie the work 'geek' by associating it with paedophiles, but I'm sure some of them will refer to themselves as geeks) when it comes to catching the Trek bug.Just a theory.Edit: After having just read Richard Berg's command above properly, I'd have to say that I believe that it's paedophile -> geek, as opposed to the other way around. People tend to be be born paedophiles, but being a technology geek seems to be a learned response.Edit2: I think we're actually arguing essentially the same thing (my brain isn't working very well this afternoon!).
